  <h2>The One Rule</h2>
  <p>
    <code>@</code> means variable. Always. Only. Everywhere.
  </p>
  <p>
    Structural keywords (like <code>init</code>, <code>if</code>, <code>case</code>, <code>end</code>) never use <code>@</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>init do
  @version: 1.0
  @major: 1

  params:
    @name: str
    @age: int

end init

Hello, @name! You are @age years old.</code></pre>

  <p>
    This compiles to a simple greeting with the variables replaced at runtime.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
